---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Introduction" activePage="Introduction">
  <style>
    .version-tag {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .version-tag__badge {
      background-color: var(--color-accent-primary);
      color: white;
      padding: 3px 10px;
      border-radius: var(--radius-full);
      font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .version-tag__date {
      color: var(--color-text-body);
    }
  </style>

  <div class="version-tag">
    <span class="version-tag__badge">v1.0</span>
    <span class="version-tag__date">Last updated: April 1, 2026</span>
  </div>

  <h1>QTE Design System</h1>
  <p>A headless, framework-agnostic design system built for <a href="https://qte.se">qte.se</a>. CSS custom properties and class-based component styles that work with any stack — React, Vue, Svelte, plain HTML, iOS (Swift), or Android (Kotlin).</p>

  <h2>Quick Start</h2>
  <h3>Install via npm</h3>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-block__copy">Copy</button>
    <code>npm install @qte/design-system</code>
  </div>

  <h3>Import tokens</h3>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-block__copy">Copy</button>
    <code>{`/* In your global CSS */
@import '@qte/design-system/tokens.css';

/* Or import specific component styles */
@import '@qte/design-system/styles/button.css';
@import '@qte/design-system/styles/card.css';`}</code>
  </div>

  <h3>Use in HTML</h3>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-block__copy">Copy</button>
    <code>{`<button class="qte-btn qte-btn--primary">
  Boka möte
</button>`}</code>
  </div>

  <h2>What's Included</h2>

  <h3>Design Tokens</h3>
  <p>49 CSS custom properties covering colors (with Light/Dark modes), spacing, border radius, typography, and shadows. All synced from Figma.</p>

  <h3>Component Styles</h3>
  <p>8 component CSS files with class-based styling. No JavaScript runtime — just CSS that works everywhere.</p>

  <h3>Accessibility</h3>
  <p>All color pairings pass WCAG AA contrast requirements. Components include focus-visible styles, keyboard navigation support, and screen reader considerations.</p>

  <h2>Architecture</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <button class="code-block__copy">Copy</button>
    <code>{`@qte/design-system/
├── tokens/          ← Source JSON (DTCG format)
├── css/tokens.css   ← CSS custom properties
├── styles/          ← Component CSS files
│   ├── button.css
│   ├── card.css
│   ├── input.css
│   ├── navigation.css
│   ├── ticker.css
│   ├── contact-list.css
│   ├── review-badge.css
│   └── footer.css
└── docs/            ← This site`}</code>
  </div>

  <h2>Work in Progress</h2>
  <p>Components and features currently in development or planned for upcoming releases.</p>

  <style>
    .wip-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
      gap: var(--spacing-md);
      margin: var(--spacing-md) 0 var(--spacing-xl);
    }
    .wip-card {
      background-color: var(--color-bg-surface);
      border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
      padding: var(--spacing-lg);
      border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200);
    }
    .wip-badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 3px 10px;
      border-radius: var(--radius-full);
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      color: white;
      margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    }
    .wip-badge--progress { background-color: var(--color-accent-primary); }
    .wip-badge--planned { background-color: #24A361; }
    .wip-badge--exploring { background-color: #D99A0A; }
    .wip-card h4 {
      font-size: var(--font-size-base);
      color: var(--color-text-heading);
      margin: 0 0 var(--spacing-xs);
    }
    .wip-card p {
      font-size: 14px;
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="wip-grid">
    <div class="wip-card">
      <span class="wip-badge wip-badge--progress">IN PROGRESS</span>
      <h4>Video Card</h4>
      <p>Card with embedded video player, poster image, play/pause overlay, and gradient frame. For case study showcases and hero sections.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="wip-card">
      <span class="wip-badge wip-badge--progress">IN PROGRESS</span>
      <h4>Motion & Animation</h4>
      <p>Animation tokens: easing curves, durations, and keyframe definitions. CSS and native platform outputs for consistent motion.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="wip-card">
      <span class="wip-badge wip-badge--planned">PLANNED</span>
      <h4>Accordion / FAQ</h4>
      <p>Expandable content sections with smooth open/close animation. For FAQ pages and long-form content organization.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="wip-card">
      <span class="wip-badge wip-badge--planned">PLANNED</span>
      <h4>Modal / Dialog</h4>
      <p>Overlay dialog with backdrop blur, focus trapping, and escape-to-close. For confirmations and booking embeds.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="wip-card">
      <span class="wip-badge wip-badge--planned">PLANNED</span>
      <h4>Toast / Notification</h4>
      <p>Temporary feedback messages (success, error, info). Auto-dismiss with progress bar. Accessible via aria-live.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="wip-card">
      <span class="wip-badge wip-badge--planned">PLANNED</span>
      <h4>Tabs</h4>
      <p>Horizontal tab navigation for switching content panels. Keyboard navigable with arrow keys.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="wip-card">
      <span class="wip-badge wip-badge--exploring">EXPLORING</span>
      <h4>Testimonial Card</h4>
      <p>Quote card with author photo, name, company, and star rating. Light pink background for social proof sections.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="wip-card">
      <span class="wip-badge wip-badge--exploring">EXPLORING</span>
      <h4>Process / Timeline</h4>
      <p>Numbered step component for project phases, delivery models, or how-it-works flows.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
